    "narrative": "Today's lineup for Ghost Ride the WHIP presents some compelling starts, led by **Mickey Moniak** and **Corbin Carroll** who boast the highest scores at 75.7 and 72.3, respectively. Both benefit from a strong combination of favorable park factors and a significant boost from dynamic platoons against opposing right-handers. **Mickey Moniak** sees an additional lift from batting second, while **Corbin Carroll**'s xwOBA of 0.372 indicates his raw projection is likely quite strong. **Tyler Soderstrom** is also in a prime spot with a score of 70.0, heavily influenced by a plus park and a glaring mismatch against a struggling opposing starter in Schultz (SP_xERA 6.23). **Max Muncy** (68.9) and **James Wood** (68.5) also stand out, with **Muncy** capitalizing on a weak opposing lefty and a potent offensive environment, while **James Wood** benefits from hitting leadoff against a hittable starter.\n\nSeveral players are receiving notable boosts beyond their base projections. **Kyle Karros** (59.5) is enjoying a significant park upgrade (+14%) and a favorable matchup against a high-ERA starter, pushing him into strong territory despite a less ideal batting order slot. Similarly, **Brice Turang** (58.4) sees his score elevated by a factor favoring stolen bases against a potentially slow-working pitcher, along with his optimal lineup spot. **Trevor Story** (57.6) is also in a good spot, with his speed factoring in positively and a decent lineup position offsetting a strong opposing arm. On the flip side, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (53.6) is somewhat hampered by a reverse platoon split today, pulling his score down from its base projection.\n\nThe most challenging bench decision today centers around **Alex Freeland**. He posted a score of 53.6, narrowly missing the cut due to a slightly lower projected efficiency compared to the starters, despite a favorable park and a decent matchup. **Jose Caballero** also presented a difficult choice, with a score of 49.7, but an elite opposing lefty in Ragans significantly capped his upside. It's worth noting that **Austin Riley**'s status is \"Lineup Pending,\" and his score of 55.7 is based on an assumed batting order; any changes to his spot could impact his day. We also have a clear warning flag with **Corbin Carroll** facing a solid right-hander in Gausman (SP_xERA 3.79), though his underlying metrics and lineup position still make him a strong play.",
